# Documentation Update Priority

## REQUIRED Updates

Documentation updates are **REQUIRED** for:
- API endpoint changes (including new endpoints)
- Database schema changes
- Data model changes
- Breaking changes to existing functionality

## RECOMMENDED Updates

Documentation updates are **RECOMMENDED** for:
- New features
- Bug fixes that change behavior
- Performance improvements that change API behavior

## Documentation Style Guidelines

- Use clear, concise descriptions
- Include code examples where helpful
- Use consistent formatting (markdown)
- Keep examples up-to-date with actual code
- Document edge cases and error conditions
- Include relevant notes and warnings

## Automatic Documentation Updates

When you make code changes, proactively:
1. Identify which documentation files are affected
2. Update them as part of the same change
3. Verify examples still work
4. Ensure consistency across all documentation files
